<chapter xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0"
         xmlns:xlink = "http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
	 lang="en">

    <title>
        Swing components
    </title>

    <example>
        <title>Demo of different widgets</title>
        <link xlink:href="http://hg.geotoolkit.org/geotoolkit/files/tip/demos/geotk-demo-samples/src/main/java/org/geotoolkit/pending/demo/swing/WidgetsDemo.java">
            <acronym>geotoolkit/demos/geotk-demo-samples/src/main/java/org/geotoolkit/pending/demo/swing/WidgetsDemo.java</acronym>
        </link>
    </example>

    <para>
        GeotoolKit offers a lot of swing components for cartography.
    </para>

    <section>
        <title>Map componants</title>

        <section>
            <title>JMap2D</title>
            <para>
                It's the first component which allow to draw maps. It uses a MapContext.
            </para>

            <figure>
                <title>
                    Displaying a map using JMap2D
                </title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/swing_jmap2d.png" format="png"></imagedata>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure>
        </section>

        <section>
            <title>JContextTree</title>
            <para>
                Show data layers, organize them, set their opacity or hide them.
            </para>

            <figure>
                <title>
                    Showing display properties using JContexTree
                </title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/swing_contexttree.png" format="png"></imagedata>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure>
        </section>

        <section>
            <title>JNavigationBar</title>
            <para>
                For navigating operations :
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>Zoom</listitem>
                    <listitem>Refresh</listitem>
                    <listitem>Zoom +</listitem>
                    <listitem>Zoom -</listitem>
                    <listitem>Pan</listitem>
                    <listitem>Go to a point</listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </para>

            <figure>
                <title>
                    Navigation bar
                </title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/swing_navtoolbar.png" format="png"></imagedata>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure>
        </section>

        <section>
            <title>JInformationBar</title>
            <para>
                Allow to get informations :
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>Measuring distance</listitem>
                    <listitem>Measuring area</listitem>
                    <listitem>Showing a popup with details about element that the mouse is hovered </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </para>

            <figure>
                <title>
                    Information bar
                </title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/swing_infotoolbar.png" format="png"></imagedata>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure>
        </section>

        <section>
            <title>JSelectionBar</title>
            <para>
                Allow selecting datas. It is possible to use differents parameters to do this (intersection testing, form of selection...).
            </para>

            <figure>
                <title>
                    Selection bar
                </title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/swing_selecttoolbar.png" format="png"></imagedata>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure>
        </section>

        <section>
            <title>JEditionBar</title>
            <para>
                Allow geometry editing.
            </para>

            <figure>
                <title>
                    Edition toolbar
                </title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/swing_edittoolbar.png" format="png"></imagedata>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure>
        </section>

        <section>
            <title>JCoordinateBar</title>
            <para>
                Show mouse coordinates, scale and allow projection change.
            </para>

            <figure>
                <title>
                    Coordinates toolbar
                </title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/swing_coordtoolbar.png" format="png"></imagedata>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure>

            <para>This one can display two additional bars, for temporal navigation and elevation.</para>

            <figure>
                <title>
                    Elevation toolbar
                </title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/swing_elevationbar.png" format="png"></imagedata>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure>

            <figure>
                <title>
                    Temporal toolbar
                </title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/swing_temporalbar.png" format="png"></imagedata>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure>
        </section>

        <section>
            <title>JConfigBar</title>
            <para>
                allows the display of decorations like the compass or the scale bar.
            </para>

            <figure>
                <title>
                    Config toolbar
                </title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/swing_conftoolbar.png" format="png"></imagedata>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure>


            <figure>
                <title>
                    Compass
                </title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/swing_northarrow.png" format="png"></imagedata>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure>

            <para>And an information panel with some parameters about the current display area.</para>

            <figure>
                <title>
                    Information panel
                </title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/swing_debug.png" format="png"></imagedata>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure>
        </section>

        <section>
            <title>JMap2DFrame</title>
            <para>
		This class can display a mini application GIS which regroup all widgets. This is useful for debuging.
            </para>

            <figure>
                <title>
                    Displaying JMap2DFrame
                </title>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/swing_jmap2dframe.png" format="png"></imagedata>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </figure>
        </section>

    </section>

    <section>
        <title>Others components</title>

        <para>Various components are also available for editing attributes or properties of different data layers whose style.</para>

        <figure>
            <title>
                window of attributes edition
            </title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="../images/swing_datatable.png" format="png"></imagedata>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>

        <figure>
            <title>
                window of style edition
            </title>
            <mediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="../images/swing_style.png" format="png"></imagedata>
                </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
        </figure>

    </section>

</chapter>